A 24-year-old South African police constable, Austin Luciano Reynold, has been found guilty for the 2018 murder of a Nigerian, Ebuka Okoli, in Durban, Kwa Zulu Natal.Okoli was shot at close range during an unauthorised raid by the police officer on the community where he resides, ChannelsTV reports.He was reportedly handcuffed, robbed and shot at close range by the officer, who was off duty at the time of the raid.Appearing before Judge Shyam Gyanda on Friday on one charge of murder and three charges of robbery, the accused was found guilty on all four charges.The tide turned on him when his accomplice in the raid turned state witness.